compute_mean_df <- function(df, effects_var_vec, response_var) {
2 
  #' Basic function to group by all factors and compute a mean
3 
  #'
4 
  #' This is called by other methods
5 ! 
  group_sym <- syms(effects_var_vec)
6 ! 
  mean_df <- df %>%
7 ! 
    group_by(!!!group_sym) %>%
8 ! 
    summarize(response_var = mean(.data[[response_var]], na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
9 ! 
    rename(!!(response_var) := response_var) %>%
10 ! 
    as.data.frame()
11 ! 
  return(mean_df)
12 
}

block_compute_df <- function(df, x_var_vec, treatment_var, response_var,

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
                             comp_func = mean, ...) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    16

                    17
                    1x
                    
                      
  group_sym <- syms(c(x_var_vec, treatment_var))

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    1x
                    
                      
  if (length(list(...)) == 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    1x
                    
                      
    block_df <- df %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    1x
                    
                      
      group_by(!!!group_sym) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    1x
                    
                      
      summarize(response_var = comp_func(.data[[response_var]], na.rm = TRUE)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    1x
                    
                      
      rename(!!(response_var) := response_var) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    1x
                    
                      
      as.data.frame()

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    !
                    
                      
    block_df <- df %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    !
                    
                      
      group_by(!!!group_sym) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    28

                    !

block_compute_box_df <- function(block_df, x_var_vec, treatment_var, response_var,

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
                                 comp_func = mean, ...) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
  # Produce the boxes

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    1x
                    
                      
  block_group_sym <- syms(x_var_vec)

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    1x
                    
                      
  block_min_df <- block_df %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    1x
                    
                      
    group_by(!!!block_group_sym) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    1x
                    
                      
    summarize(response_min = min(.data[[response_var]], na.rm = TRUE)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    1x
                    
                      
    as.data.frame()

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    1x
                    
                      
  block_max_df <- block_df %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    1x
                    
                      
    group_by(!!!block_group_sym) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    1x
                    
                      
    summarize(response_max = max(.data[[response_var]], na.rm = TRUE)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    1x
                    
                      
    as.data.frame()

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    1x
                    
                      
  block_box_df <- merge(block_min_df, block_max_df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    1x
                    
                      
  block_box_df$response_mid <- (block_box_df$response_max + block_box_df$response_min) / 2

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    
                    
                      
  # height_buffer is proportional to the height of the window

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    1x
                    
                      
  height_buffer <- 0.05 * (max(block_box_df$response_max) - min(block_box_df$response_min))

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    1x
                    
                      
  block_box_df$response_height <- (block_box_df$response_max - block_box_df$response_min) +

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    1x
                    
                      
    height_buffer

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    1x
                    
                      
  return(block_box_df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    
                    
                      
}

binom_p_value_br <- function(sign_test_df_row_part, alpha = 0.05) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    131
                    !
                    
                      
  bin_conf_level <- 1 - alpha

                    		
                  

                  

                    132
                    !
                    
                      
  temp_out <- binom.test(sign_test_df_row_part[1],

                    		
                  

                  

                    133
                    !
                    
                      
    sign_test_df_row_part[2],

                    		
                  

                  

                    134
                    !
                    
                      
    p = 0.5, alternative = "two.sided",

                    		
                  

                  

                    135
                    !
                    
                      
    conf.level = bin_conf_level

                    		
                  

                  

                    136
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    137
                    !
                    
                      
  p_val <- temp_out$p.value

                    		
                  

                  

                    138
                    !
                    
                      
  return(p_val)

                    		
                  

                  

                    139
                    
                    
                      
}

sign_test_compute_df <- function(df, x_var_vec, treatment_var, response_var,

                    		
                  

                  

                    142
                    
                    
                      
                                 higher_is_better = TRUE, use_margins = TRUE, alpha = 0.05,

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    
                    
                      
                                 p_adj = "bonferonni",

                    		
                  

                  

                    144
                    
                    
                      
                                 comp_func = mean, ...) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    145
                    
                    
                      
  #' Computes a sign test rank df from the block plot

                    		
                  

                  

                    146
                    
                    
                      
  #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    147
                    
                    
                      
  #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    148
                    
                    
                      
  #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    149
                    
                    
                      
  #'

                    		
                  

                  

                    150
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    151
                    
                    
                      
  # This uses the block_df computed from block_compute_df()

                    		
                  

                  

                    152
                    !
                    
                      
  block_df <- block_compute_df(

                    		
                  

                  

                    153
                    !
                    
                      
    df, x_var_vec, treatment_var, response_var,

                    		
                  

                  

                    154
                    !
                    
                      
    comp_func, ...

                    		
                  

                  

                    155
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    156
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    157
                    !
                    
                      
  sign_test_df <- data.frame(

                    		
                  

                  

                    158
                    !
                    
                      
    treatment_1 = character(),

                    		
                  

                  

                    159
                    !
                    
                      
    treatment_2 = character(),

                    		
                  

                  

                    160
                    !
                    
                      
    num_comparisons = numeric(),

                    		
                  

                  

                    161
                    !
                    
                      
    num_1_better_or_equal_than_2 = numeric(),

                    		
                  

                  

                    162
                    !
                    
                      
    num_1_equal_to_2 = numeric(),

                    		
                  

                  

                    163
                    !
                    
                      
    stringsAsFactors = FALSE

                    		
                  

                  

                    164
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    165
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    166
                    
                    
                      
  # Enumerate all combinations of levels. If a mean is missing, put NA for the Effect

                    		
                  

                  

                    167
                    
                    
                      
  # picking an arbitrary one of the two as Maximum.

                    		
                  

                  

                    168
                    
                    
                      
  # Design choice: Use unique options rather than levels

                    		
                  

                  

                    169
                    !
                    
                      
  var_levels <- unique(df[[treatment_var]])

                    		
                  

                  

                    170
                    !
                    
                      
  curr_options <- t(combn(var_levels, 2))

                    		
                  

                  

                    171
                    !
                    
                      
  num_comparisons <- 0

                    		
                  

                  

                    172
                    !
                    
                      
  num_1_better_or_equal_than_2 <- 0

                    		
                  

                  

                    173
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    174
                    !
                    
                      
  treatment_var_1 <- paste(treatment_var, "1", sep = "_")

                    		
                  

                  

                    175
                    !
                    
                      
  treatment_var_2 <- paste(treatment_var, "2", sep = "_")

                    		
                  

                  

                    176
                    !
                    
                      
  response_var_1 <- paste(response_var, "1", sep = "_")

                    		
                  

                  

                    177
                    !
                    
                      
  response_var_2 <- paste(response_var, "2", sep = "_")

                    		
                  

                  

                    178
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    179
                    !
                    
                      
  for (r in seq_len(nrow(curr_options))) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    180
                    !
                    
                      
    treatment_1 <- curr_options[r, 1]

                    		
                  

                  

                    181
                    !
                    
                      
    treatment_2 <- curr_options[r, 2]

                    		
                  

                  

                    182
                    !
                    
                      
    t1_df <- block_df[block_df[[treatment_var]] == treatment_1, ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    183
                    !
                    
                      
    t2_df <- block_df[block_df[[treatment_var]] == treatment_2, ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    184
                    !
                    
                      
    colnames(t1_df)[which(names(t1_df) == treatment_var)] <- treatment_var_1

                    		
                  

                  

                    185
                    !
                    
                      
    colnames(t2_df)[which(names(t2_df) == treatment_var)] <- treatment_var_2

                    		
                  

                  

                    186
                    !
                    
                      
    colnames(t1_df)[which(names(t1_df) == response_var)] <- response_var_1

                    		
                  

                  

                    187
                    !
                    
                      
    colnames(t2_df)[which(names(t2_df) == response_var)] <- response_var_2

                    		
                  

                  

                    188
                    !
                    
                      
    t_df <- merge(t1_df, t2_df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    189
                    !
                    
                      
    t_df$diff <- t_df[[response_var_1]] - t_df[[response_var_2]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    190
                    !
                    
                      
    num_comparisons <- nrow(t_df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    191
                    !
                    
                      
    num_ge_comparisons <- nrow(t_df[t_df$diff >= 0, ])

                    		
                  

                  

                    192
                    !
                    
                      
    num_le_comparisons <- nrow(t_df[t_df$diff <= 0, ])

                    		
                  

                  

                    193
                    !
                    
                      
    num_eq_comparisons <- nrow(t_df[t_df$diff == 0, ])

                    		
                  

                  

                    194
                    !
                    
                      
    num_1_better_or_equal_than_2 <- nrow(t_df[])

                    		
                  

                  

                    195
                    
                    
                      
    # Now construct two rows from this computation, switching these axes

                    		
                  

                  

                    196
                    !
                    
                      
    curr_1_row <- c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    197
                    !
                    
                      
      as.character(treatment_1), as.character(treatment_2),

                    		
                  

                  

                    198
                    !
                    
                      
      num_comparisons, num_ge_comparisons, num_eq_comparisons

                    		
                  

                  

                    199
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    200
                    !
                    
                      
    curr_2_row <- c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    201
                    !
                    
                      
      as.character(treatment_2), as.character(treatment_1),

                    		
                  

                  

                    202
                    !
                    
                      
      num_comparisons, num_le_comparisons, num_eq_comparisons

                    		
                  

                  

                    203
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    204
                    !
                    
                      
    if (!higher_is_better) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    205
                    !
                    
                      
      curr_1_row <- c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    206
                    !
                    
                      
        as.character(treatment_1), as.character(treatment_2),

                    		
                  

                  

                    207
                    !
                    
                      
        num_comparisons, num_le_comparisons, num_eq_comparisons

                    		
                  

                  

                    208
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    209
                    !
                    
                      
      curr_2_row <- c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    210
                    !
                    
                      
        as.character(treatment_2), as.character(treatment_1),

                    		
                  

                  

                    211
                    !
                    
                      
        num_comparisons, num_ge_comparisons, num_eq_comparisons

                    		
                  

                  

                    212
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    213
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    214
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    215
                    !
                    
                      
    sign_test_df <- rbind(sign_test_df, curr_1_row)

                    		
                  

                  

                    216
                    !
                    
                      
    names(sign_test_df) <- c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    217
                    !
                    
                      
      "treatment_1", "treatment_2",

                    		
                  

                  

                    218
                    !
                    
                      
      "num_comparisons", "num_1_better_or_equal_than_2",

                    		
                  

                  

                    219
                    !
                    
                      
      "num_1_equal_to_2"

                    		
                  

                  

                    220
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    221
                    !
                    
                      
    sign_test_df <- rbind(sign_test_df, curr_2_row)

                    		
                  

                  

                    222
                    !
                    
                      
    names(sign_test_df) <- c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    223
                    !
                    
                      
      "treatment_1", "treatment_2",

                    		
                  

                  

                    224
                    !
                    
                      
      "num_comparisons", "num_1_better_or_equal_than_2",

                    		
                  

                  

                    225
                    !
                    
                      
      "num_1_equal_to_2"

                    		
                  

                  

                    226
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    227
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    228
                    !
                    
                      
  sign_test_df$treatment_1 <- factor(sign_test_df$treatment_1,

                    		
                  

                  

                    229
                    !
                    
                      
    levels = levels(df[[treatment_var]])

                    		
                  

                  

                    230
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    231
                    !
                    
                      
  sign_test_df$treatment_2 <- factor(sign_test_df$treatment_2,

                    		
                  

                  

                    232
                    !
                    
                      
    levels = levels(df[[treatment_var]])

                    		
                  

                  

                    233
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    234
                    !
                    
                      
  sign_test_df$num_comparisons <- as.numeric(sign_test_df$num_comparisons)

                    		
                  

                  

                    235
                    !
                    
                      
  sign_test_df$num_1_better_or_equal_than_2 <-

                    		
                  

                  

                    236
                    !
                    
                      
    as.numeric(sign_test_df$num_1_better_or_equal_than_2)

                    		
                  

                  

                    237
                    !
                    
                      
  sign_test_df$num_1_equal_to_2 <- as.numeric(sign_test_df$num_1_equal_to_2)

                    		
                  

                  

                    238
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    239
                    
                    
                      
  # Get levels for the treatment in descending order of total number of geq comparisons

                    		
                  

                  

                    240
                    !
                    
                      
  block_sum_df <- aggregate(num_1_better_or_equal_than_2 ~ treatment_1,

                    		
                  

                  

                    241
                    !
                    
                      
    data = sign_test_df, FUN = sum, na.rm = TRUE

                    		
                  

                  

                    242
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    243
                    !
                    
                      
  block_sum_df <- block_sum_df[order(-block_sum_df$num_1_better_or_equal_than_2), ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    244
                    !
                    
                      
  treatment_levels <- rev(unique(block_sum_df$treatment_1))

                    		
                  

                  

                    245
                    !
                    
                      
  sign_test_df$treatment_1 <- factor(sign_test_df$treatment_1,

                    		
                  

                  

                    246
                    !
                    
                      
    levels = treatment_levels

                    		
                  

                  

                    247
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    248
                    !
                    
                      
  sign_test_df$treatment_2 <- factor(sign_test_df$treatment_2,

                    		
                  

                  

                    249
                    !
                    
                      
    levels = treatment_levels

                    		
                  

                  

                    250
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    251
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    252
                    !
                    
                      
  if (use_margins) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    253
                    !
                    
                      
    block_sum_df <- aggregate(

                    		
                  

                  

                    254
                    !
                    
                      
      cbind(

                    		
                  

                  

                    255
                    !
                    
                      
        num_1_better_or_equal_than_2, num_1_equal_to_2,

                    		
                  

                  

                    256
                    !
                    
                      
        num_comparisons

                    		
                  

                  

                    257
                    !
                    
                      
      ) ~ treatment_1,

                    		
                  

                  

                    258
                    !
                    
                      
      data = sign_test_df, FUN = sum, na.rm = TRUE

                    		
                  

                  

                    259
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    260
                    !
                    
                      
    block_sum_df <- block_sum_df[order(-block_sum_df$num_1_better_or_equal_than_2), ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    261
                    !
                    
                      
    block_sum_df$treatment_2 <- "(all)"

                    		
                  

                  

                    262
                    !
                    
                      
    treatment_levels <- c("(all)", rev(unique(as.character(block_sum_df$treatment_1))))

                    		
                  

                  

                    263
                    
                    
                      
    # Append the sum to sign test rank

                    		
                  

                  

                    264
                    !
                    
                      
    block_sum_df <- block_sum_df[, names(sign_test_df)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    265
                    !
                    
                      
    sign_test_df <- rbind(sign_test_df, block_sum_df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    266
                    !
                    
                      
    sign_test_df$treatment_1 <- factor(as.character(sign_test_df$treatment_1),

                    		
                  

                  

                    267
                    !
                    
                      
      levels = treatment_levels

                    		
                  

                  

                    268
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    269
                    !
                    
                      
    sign_test_df$treatment_2 <- factor(as.character(sign_test_df$treatment_2),

                    		
                  

                  

                    270
                    !
                    
                      
      levels = treatment_levels

                    		
                  

                  

                    271
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    272
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    273
                    !
                    
                      
  sign_test_df$frac_1_better_or_equal_than_2 <-

                    		
                  

                  

                    274
                    !
                    
                      
    sign_test_df$num_1_better_or_equal_than_2 / sign_test_df$num_comparisons

                    		
                  

                  

                    275
                    !
                    
                      
  sign_test_df$frac_1_equal_to_2 <-

                    		
                  

                  

                    276
                    !
                    
                      
    sign_test_df$num_1_equal_to_2 / sign_test_df$num_comparisons

                    		
                  

                  

                    277
                    !
                    
                      
  sign_test_df$num_1_better_than_2 <-

                    		
                  

                  

                    278
                    !
                    
                      
    sign_test_df$num_1_better_or_equal_than_2 - sign_test_df$num_1_equal_to_2

                    		
                  

                  

                    279
                    !
                    
                      
  sign_test_df$frac_1_better_than_2 <-

                    		
                  

                  

                    280
                    !
                    
                      
    sign_test_df$num_1_better_than_2 / sign_test_df$num_comparisons

                    		
                  

                  

                    281
                    
                    
                      
  # Get p-values

                    		
                  

                  

                    282
                    !
                    
                      
  sign_test_df$p_values <- apply(

                    		
                  

                  

                    283
                    !
                    
                      
    sign_test_df[, c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    284
                    !
                    
                      
      "num_1_better_or_equal_than_2",

                    		
                  

                  

                    285
                    !
                    
                      
      "num_comparisons"

                    		
                  

                  

                    286
                    
                    
                      
    )],

                    		
                  

                  

                    287
                    !
                    
                      
    MARGIN = 1, FUN = binom_p_value_br, alpha = alpha

                    		
                  

                  

                    288
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    289
                    !
                    
                      
  sign_test_df$p_values_str <- apply(sign_test_df[, c("num_1_better_than_2", "num_comparisons")],

                    		
                  

                  

                    290
                    !
                    
                      
    MARGIN = 1, FUN = binom_p_value_br, alpha = alpha

                    		
                  

                  

                    291
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    292
                    !
                    
                      
  sign_test_df$p_values_bf_adj <- NA

                    		
                  

                  

                    293
                    !
                    
                      
  sign_test_df[sign_test_df$treatment_2 != "(all)", ]$p_values_bf_adj <-

                    		
                  

                  

                    294
                    !
                    
                      
    p.adjust(sign_test_df[sign_test_df$treatment_2 != "(all)", ]$p_values, method = "bonferroni")

                    		
                  

                  

                    295
                    !
                    
                      
  sign_test_df$p_values_str_bf_adj <- NA

                    		
                  

                  

                    296
                    !
                    
                      
  sign_test_df[sign_test_df$treatment_2 != "(all)", ]$p_values_str_bf_adj <-

                    		
                  

                  

                    297
                    !
                    
                      
    p.adjust(sign_test_df[sign_test_df$treatment_2 != "(all)", ]$p_values_str,

                    		
                  

                  

                    298
                    !
                    
                      
      method = "bonferroni"

                    		
                  

                  

                    299
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    300
                    !
                    
                      
  if (use_margins) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    301
                    !
                    
                      
    sign_test_df[sign_test_df$treatment_2 == "(all)", ]$p_values <- NA

                    		
                  

                  

                    302
                    !
                    
                      
    sign_test_df[sign_test_df$treatment_2 == "(all)", ]$p_values_bf_adj <- NA

                    		
                  

                  

                    303
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    304
                    !
                    
                      
  return(sign_test_df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    305
                    
                    
                      
}

sign_test_produce_plot <- function(sign_test_df, x_var_vec, treatment_var, response_var,

                    		
                  

                  

                    308

tile_table_count_df <- function(df, x_fac_vec, y_fac_vec, response_name = "count",

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
                                digits = 2, use_margins = FALSE, remove_NA_factors = FALSE) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    !
                    
                      
  treatment_fac <- x_fac_vec[1]

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    !
                    
                      
  fac_vec <- y_fac_vec

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    !
                    
                      
  if (length(x_fac_vec) >= 2) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    !
                    
                      
    fac_vec <- c(x_fac_vec[2:length(x_fac_vec)], y_fac_vec)

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    !
                    
                      
  group_sym <- syms(c(fac_vec, treatment_fac))

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    !
                    
                      
  count_df <- df %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::count(!!!group_sym, .drop = FALSE) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    !
                    
                      
    as.data.frame()

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    !
                    
                      
  names(count_df)[names(count_df) == "n"] <- response_name

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    !
                    
                      
  if (remove_NA_factors) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    !
                    
                      
    count_df <- na.omit(count_df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
  # Add x-axis and y-axis margins if desired

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
  # For ease of display, we add the margins to the data frame with an (all) variable

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    !
                    
                      
  if (use_margins) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
    # Produce the aggregated data frame

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    !
                    
                      
    global_mean <- mean(count_df[[response_name]])

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    !
                    
                      
    group_x_sym <- syms(c(x_fac_vec))

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    !
                    
                      
    x_mar_df <- count_df %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    !
                    
                      
      group_by(!!!group_x_sym) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::summarize(response_name = mean(.data[[response_name]], na.rm = TRUE)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    !
                    
                      
      rename(!!(response_name) := response_name) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    !
                    
                      
      as.data.frame()

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    !
                    
                      
    group_y_sym <- syms(c(y_fac_vec))

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    !
                    
                      
    y_mar_df <- count_df %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    !
                    
                      
      group_by(!!!group_y_sym) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::summarize(response_name = mean(.data[[response_name]], na.rm = TRUE)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    !
                    
                      
      rename(!!(response_name) := response_name) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    !
                    
                      
      as.data.frame()

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    !
                    
                      
    mar_df <- plyr::rbind.fill(count_df, x_mar_df, y_mar_df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    !
                    
                      
    for (x_fac in x_fac_vec) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    !
                    
                      
      prev_levels <- levels(mar_df[[x_fac]])

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    !
                    
                      
      new_levels <- c(prev_levels, "(all)")

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    !
                    
                      
      mar_df[[x_fac]] <- as.character(mar_df[[x_fac]])

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    !
                    
                      
      mar_df[[x_fac]][is.na(mar_df[[x_fac]])] <- "(all)"

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    !
                    
                      
      mar_df[[x_fac]] <- factor(mar_df[[x_fac]], levels = new_levels)

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    !
                    
                      
    for (y_fac in y_fac_vec) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    !
                    
                      
      prev_levels <- levels(mar_df[[y_fac]])

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    !
                    
                      
      new_levels <- c(prev_levels, "(all)")

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    !
                    
                      
      mar_df[[y_fac]] <- as.character(mar_df[[y_fac]])

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    !
                    
                      
      mar_df[[y_fac]][is.na(mar_df[[y_fac]])] <- "(all)"

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    !
                    
                      
      mar_df[[y_fac]] <- factor(mar_df[[y_fac]], levels = new_levels)

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    !
                    
                      
    global_vec <- c(rep("(all)", length(x_fac_vec) + length(y_fac_vec)), global_mean)

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    !
                    
                      
    mar_df <- rbind(mar_df, global_vec)

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    !
                    
                      
    mar_df[[response_name]] <- as.numeric(mar_df[[response_name]])

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    !
                    
                      
    count_df <- mar_df

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    !
                    
                      
  count_df[[response_name]] <- round(count_df[[response_name]], digits = digits)

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    !
                    
                      
  return(count_df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    
                    
                      
}

tile_tf_count_df <- function(df, fac_vec, response_name = "count",

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    
                    
                      
                             digits = 2, remove_NA_factors = FALSE) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    !
                    
                      
  tf_df <- data.frame(

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    !
                    
                      
    x_fac = character(), y_fac = character(),

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    !
                    
                      
    x_scale = character(), y_scale = character(),

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    !
                    
                      
    count = integer(), stringsAsFactors = FALSE

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    
                    
                      
  # First do uni-factor counts

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    !
                    
                      
  for (fac in fac_vec) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    !
                    
                      
    group_sym <- syms(c(fac))

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    !
                    
                      
    count_df <- df %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::count(!!!group_sym, .drop = FALSE) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    !
                    
                      
      as.data.frame()

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    !
                    
                      
    names(count_df)[names(count_df) == "n"] <- response_name

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    !
                    
                      
    count_df$x_fac <- fac

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    !
                    
                      
    count_df$y_fac <- fac

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    !
                    
                      
    colnames(count_df)[which(names(count_df) == fac)] <- "x_scale"

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    !
                    
                      
    count_df$x_scale <- as.character(count_df$x_scale)

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    !
                    
                      
    count_df$y_scale <- as.character(count_df$x_scale)

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    !
                    
                      
    count_df <- count_df[, c("x_fac", "y_fac", "x_scale", "y_scale", "count")]

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    !
                    
                      
    tf_df <- rbind(tf_df, count_df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    
                    
                      
  # Now do two-level interaction counts

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    !
                    
                      
  for (fac_comb in combn(fac_vec, 2, simplify = FALSE)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    !
                    
                      
    group_sym <- syms(c(fac_comb))

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    !
                    
                      
    count_df <- df %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::count(!!!group_sym, .drop = FALSE) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    !
                    
                      
      as.data.frame()

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    !
                    
                      
    names(count_df)[names(count_df) == "n"] <- response_name

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    !
                    
                      
    count_b_df <- count_df

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    
                    
                      
    # One direction of the combination

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    !
                    
                      
    x_fac <- fac_comb[1]

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    !
                    
                      
    y_fac <- fac_comb[2]

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    !
                    
                      
    count_df$x_fac <- x_fac

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    !
                    
                      
    count_df$y_fac <- y_fac

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    !
                    
                      
    colnames(count_df)[which(names(count_df) == x_fac)] <- "x_scale"

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    !
                    
                      
    colnames(count_df)[which(names(count_df) == y_fac)] <- "y_scale"

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    !
                    
                      
    count_df$x_scale <- as.character(count_df$x_scale)

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    !
                    
                      
    count_df$y_scale <- as.character(count_df$y_scale)

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    !
                    
                      
    count_df <- count_df[, c("x_fac", "y_fac", "x_scale", "y_scale", "count")]

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    !
                    
                      
    tf_df <- rbind(tf_df, count_df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    
                    
                      
    # Other direction of the combination

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    !
                    
                      
    count_b_df$x_fac <- y_fac

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    !
                    
                      
    count_b_df$y_fac <- x_fac

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    !
                    
                      
    colnames(count_b_df)[which(names(count_b_df) == y_fac)] <- "x_scale"

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    !
                    
                      
    colnames(count_b_df)[which(names(count_b_df) == x_fac)] <- "y_scale"

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    !
                    
                      
    count_b_df$x_scale <- as.character(count_b_df$x_scale)

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    !
                    
                      
    count_b_df$y_scale <- as.character(count_b_df$y_scale)

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    !
                    
                      
    count_b_df <- count_b_df[, c("x_fac", "y_fac", "x_scale", "y_scale", "count")]

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    !
                    
                      
    tf_df <- rbind(tf_df, count_b_df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    !
                    
                      
  tf_df$x_fac <- as.factor(tf_df$x_fac)

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    !
                    
                      
  tf_df$y_fac <- as.factor(tf_df$y_fac)

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    !
                    
                      
  tf_df$x_scale <- as.factor(tf_df$x_scale)

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    !
                    
                      
  tf_df$y_scale <- as.factor(tf_df$y_scale)

                    		
                  

                  

                    113
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    114
                    !
                    
                      
  if (remove_NA_factors) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    115
                    !
                    
                      
    tf_df <- na.omit(tf_df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    116
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    117
                    !
                    
                      
  tf_df[[response_name]] <- round(tf_df[[response_name]], digits = digits)

                    		
                  

                  

                    118
                    !
                    
                      
  return(tf_df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    119
                    
                    
                      
}

tile_tf_compute_df <- function(df, fac_vec, response_var,

                    		
                  

                  

                    123
                    
                    
                      
                               digits = 2, remove_NA_factors = FALSE) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    124
                    !
                    
                      
  tf_df <- data.frame(

                    		
                  

                  

                    125
                    !
                    
                      
    x_fac = character(), y_fac = character(),

                    		
                  

                  

                    126
                    !
                    
                      
    x_scale = character(), y_scale = character(),

                    		
                  

                  

                    127
                    !
                    
                      
    response = integer(), stringsAsFactors = FALSE

                    		
                  

                  

                    128
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    129
                    !
                    
                      
  names(tf_df)[names(tf_df) == "response"] <- response_var

                    		
                  

                  

                    130
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    131
                    
                    
                      
  # First do uni-factor counts

                    		
                  

                  

                    132
                    !
                    
                      
  for (fac in fac_vec) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    133
                    !
                    
                      
    group_sym <- syms(c(fac))

                    		
                  

                  

                    134
                    !
                    
                      
    resp_df <- df %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    135
                    !
                    
                      
      group_by(!!!group_sym) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    136
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::summarize(response_var = mean(.data[[response_var]], na.rm = TRUE)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    137
                    !
                    
                      
      rename(!!(response_var) := response_var) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    138
                    !

                    139
                    !
                    
                      
    resp_df$x_fac <- fac

                    		
                  

                  

                    140
                    !
                    
                      
    resp_df$y_fac <- fac

                    		
                  

                  

                    141
                    !
                    
                      
    colnames(resp_df)[which(names(resp_df) == fac)] <- "x_scale"

                    		
                  

                  

                    142
                    !
                    
                      
    resp_df$x_scale <- as.character(resp_df$x_scale)

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    !
                    
                      
    resp_df$y_scale <- as.character(resp_df$x_scale)

                    		
                  

                  

                    144
                    !
                    
                      
    resp_df <- resp_df[, c("x_fac", "y_fac", "x_scale", "y_scale", response_var)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    145
                    !
                    
                      
    tf_df <- rbind(tf_df, resp_df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    146
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    147
                    
                    
                      
  # Now do two-level interaction counts

                    		
                  

                  

                    148
                    !
                    
                      
  for (fac_comb in combn(fac_vec, 2, simplify = FALSE)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    149
                    !
                    
                      
    group_sym <- syms(c(fac_comb))

                    		
                  

                  

                    150
                    !
                    
                      
    resp_df <- df %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    151
                    !
                    
                      
      group_by(!!!group_sym) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    152
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::summarize(response_var = mean(.data[[response_var]], na.rm = TRUE)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    153
                    !
                    
                      
      rename(!!(response_var) := response_var) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    154
                    !
                    
                      
      as.data.frame()

                    		
                  

                  

                    155
                    !
                    
                      
    resp_b_df <- resp_df

                    		
                  

                  

                    156
                    
                    
                      
    # One direction of the combination

                    		
                  

                  

                    157
                    !
                    
                      
    x_fac <- fac_comb[1]

                    		
                  

                  

                    158
                    !
                    
                      
    y_fac <- fac_comb[2]

                    		
                  

                  

                    159
                    !
                    
                      
    resp_df$x_fac <- x_fac

                    		
                  

                  

                    160
                    !
                    
                      
    resp_df$y_fac <- y_fac

                    		
                  

                  

                    161
                    !
                    
                      
    colnames(resp_df)[which(names(resp_df) == x_fac)] <- "x_scale"

                    		
                  

                  

                    162
                    !
                    
                      
    colnames(resp_df)[which(names(resp_df) == y_fac)] <- "y_scale"

                    		
                  

                  

                    163
                    !
                    
                      
    resp_df$x_scale <- as.character(resp_df$x_scale)

                    !

                    168

                    169

                    170

    colnames(resp_b_df)[which(names(resp_b_df) == x_fac)] <- "y_scale"

    resp_b_df$x_scale <- as.character(resp_b_df$x_scale)

                    !
                    
                      
    resp_b_df$y_scale <- as.character(resp_b_df$y_scale)

    resp_b_df <- resp_b_df[, c("x_fac", "y_fac", "x_scale", "y_scale", response_var)]

  tf_df$x_fac <- as.factor(tf_df$x_fac)

                    		
                  

                  

                    178
                    !
                    
                      
  tf_df$y_fac <- as.factor(tf_df$y_fac)

                    		
                  

                  

                    179
                    !
                    
                      
  tf_df$x_scale <- as.factor(tf_df$x_scale)

                    		
                  

                  

                    180

  tf_df$y_scale <- as.factor(tf_df$y_scale)

                    		
                  

                  

                    181
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    182

  if (remove_NA_factors) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    183
                    !
                    
                      
    tf_df <- na.omit(tf_df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    184
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    185
                    !
                    
                      
  tf_df[[response_var]] <- round(tf_df[[response_var]], digits = digits)

  return(tf_df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    187
                    
                    
                      
}
